00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:42,230 --> 00:00:46,068
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

2
00:00:46,151 --> 00:00:50,947
FIVE HOURS BEFORE THE FLIGHT

3
00:00:54,034 --> 00:00:55,661
You like Luwak coffee, Ms. Mo?

4
00:00:55,744 --> 00:00:57,037
Yes, I do.

5
00:00:57,120 --> 00:00:59,206
I enjoy it as a drip brew sometimes.

6
00:00:59,289 --> 00:01:00,666
What about you?

7
00:01:00,749 --> 00:01:01,667
I used to,

8
00:01:01,750 --> 00:01:03,877
until a business trip
to Bali three years ago.

9
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:06,421
I went for a raw materials survey
and caught the first flight back.

10
00:01:06,505 --> 00:01:07,506
Why?

11
00:01:07,589 --> 00:01:09,341
It just rubbed me the wrong way.

12
00:01:09,841 --> 00:01:12,552
That expensive coffee
is made from cat poop, after all.

13
00:01:13,804 --> 00:01:16,098
I couldn't drink it
once I saw it for myself.

14
00:01:16,181 --> 00:01:18,475
The same applies here.
I could have dated you in ignorance,

15
00:01:18,558 --> 00:01:21,770
but the truth won't allow it now, you see.

16
00:01:22,646 --> 00:01:24,231
It sounds like you're upset.

17
00:01:24,314 --> 00:01:25,941
Marriage is a lifelong business.

18
00:01:26,024 --> 00:01:27,984
Shouldn't trust be paramount?

19
00:01:29,403 --> 00:01:31,446
You should pay for the coffee.

20
00:01:32,072 --> 00:01:33,824
Let's call it a damages settlement.

21
00:01:34,991 --> 00:01:36,702
-Hold on.
-Right.

22
00:01:38,245 --> 00:01:40,789
Just a heads up.
You should go somewhere else for lunch.

23
00:01:40,872 --> 00:01:43,083
I have a blind date
on the second floor in ten minutes.

24
00:01:43,166 --> 00:01:45,252
I'm all about efficiency,

25
00:01:45,335 --> 00:01:47,212
so I figured I'd kill two birds
with one stone.

26
00:01:47,295 --> 00:01:48,714
Don't be too offended.

27
00:01:59,099 --> 00:02:00,225
Se-gye!

28
00:02:01,476 --> 00:02:02,728
That blind date

29
00:02:03,353 --> 00:02:04,604
is with me.

30
00:02:05,439 --> 00:02:07,399
Give me a chance to apologize properly.

31
00:02:09,484 --> 00:02:10,485
What's going on here?

32
00:02:10,569 --> 00:02:13,989
I fail to see why you must insist
on this union.

33
00:02:15,282 --> 00:02:17,117
Mochang's value-driven approach

34
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:18,618
and Chail's formidable tech assets

35
00:02:18,702 --> 00:02:20,579
would make a perfectly synergistic pair.

36
00:02:20,662 --> 00:02:22,122
When the need is this great,

37
00:02:22,205 --> 00:02:24,833
even broken trust might be
worth rebuilding.

38
00:02:25,959 --> 00:02:27,335
You've never lost, have you?

39
00:02:28,003 --> 00:02:29,963
No. I don't recall
any losses in particular.

40
00:02:30,046 --> 00:02:32,716
You've never known defeat or loss.

41
00:02:32,799 --> 00:02:35,552
Life isn't particularly easy,
but it's not too hard either.

42
00:02:35,635 --> 00:02:38,305
Even so, you're only satisfied
when you get what you need.

43
00:02:38,388 --> 00:02:40,223
Is that a bad thing?

44
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:43,018
Not necessarily.

45
00:02:45,270 --> 00:02:48,273
I can't stand people who don't know jack,
meddle in everything,

46
00:02:48,356 --> 00:02:52,360
and insist on wallowing
in their entitlement.

47
00:02:56,490 --> 00:02:59,242
Since it appears you're a woman
who shares my values,

48
00:02:59,326 --> 00:03:02,996
I guess we can skip
the needless mind games and runaround.

49
00:03:08,877 --> 00:03:11,046
You're toxic, like poison.

50
00:03:12,255 --> 00:03:13,215
Cha Se-gye!

51
00:03:13,298 --> 00:03:14,341
Have you gone mad?

52
00:03:14,966 --> 00:03:16,843
Cha Se-gye! Open your eyes!

53
00:03:16,927 --> 00:03:19,971
<i>I can't stand people who don't know jack,</i>
<i>meddle in everything…</i>

54
00:03:21,598 --> 00:03:25,060
<i>and insist on wallowing</i>
<i>in their entitlement.</i>

55
00:03:25,143 --> 00:03:27,854
-Cha Se-gye, no!
-One, two, three!

56
00:03:36,655 --> 00:03:38,011
Oh no…

57
00:03:38,698 --> 00:03:41,326
<i>Since it appears you're a woman</i>
<i>who shares my values,</i>

58
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:43,912
<i>I guess we can skip</i>

59
00:03:44,496 --> 00:03:47,082
<i>the needless mind games and runaround.</i>

60
00:03:51,962 --> 00:03:52,921
<i>Passengers,</i>

61
00:03:53,004 --> 00:03:56,174
<i>we will soon be arriving</i>
<i>at Jeju International Airport.</i>

62
00:03:56,258 --> 00:03:57,801
<i>Please fasten your seatbelts…</i>

63
00:03:59,845 --> 00:04:01,388
<i>No feelings, my foot.</i>

64
00:04:03,807 --> 00:04:07,435
EPISODE 6
ONE MAGICAL NIGHT

65
00:04:17,112 --> 00:04:18,530
<i>All white walls</i>

66
00:04:19,155 --> 00:04:21,408
<i>and nothing but white everywhere…</i>

67
00:04:22,117 --> 00:04:23,159
<i>Could this be…</i>

68
00:04:23,243 --> 00:04:24,661
Have I finally…

69
00:04:26,830 --> 00:04:29,291
crossed over to the afterlife?

70
00:04:32,794 --> 00:04:33,962
I see no hellfire.

71
00:04:35,422 --> 00:04:37,883
No King of Hell either.

72
00:04:39,759 --> 00:04:41,052
Paradise?

73
00:04:44,306 --> 00:04:45,432
My goodness!

74
00:04:45,932 --> 00:04:47,392
No, I am in hell.

75
00:04:49,352 --> 00:04:50,562
Oh no…

76
00:04:51,313 --> 00:04:53,440
Hey. Are you awake?

77
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:56,526
I see I am still alive.

78
00:04:56,610 --> 00:04:58,987
Man, you really scared me.

79
00:04:59,779 --> 00:05:01,656
Who gets electrocuted on a plane?

80
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:04,284
Talk about a hardcore first day.

81
00:05:04,367 --> 00:05:06,494
We are still alive, so cease your fussing.

82
00:05:07,621 --> 00:05:08,788
What of Cha Se-gye?

83
00:05:08,872 --> 00:05:10,373
What has become of Cha Se-gye?

84
00:05:10,999 --> 00:05:14,628
Your pre-flight medication
didn't contain the substance,

85
00:05:14,711 --> 00:05:17,923
but your blood test indicates
digitoxin poisoning,

86
00:05:18,006 --> 00:05:20,091
resulting in acute cardiac arrest.

87
00:05:20,175 --> 00:05:21,343
Is that a poison?

88
00:05:21,426 --> 00:05:24,763
It is a digitalis-extracted compound
primarily used as a cardiac stimulant.

89
00:05:24,846 --> 00:05:28,224
It's used to treat heart failure,
arrhythmia, and epilepsy.

90
00:05:28,308 --> 00:05:31,436
We've administered the antidote,
so just rest up for a day,

91
00:05:31,519 --> 00:05:34,856
and you should be able to resume
daily activities without any issue.

92
00:05:34,940 --> 00:05:35,941
What about…

93
00:05:36,858 --> 00:05:37,943
What about her?

94
00:05:38,485 --> 00:05:39,945
-Is she okay?
-Who exactly?

95
00:05:40,028 --> 00:05:42,614
A woman should've been brought in with me.

96
00:05:42,697 --> 00:05:43,573
Shin Seo-ri.

97
00:05:43,657 --> 00:05:46,576
I'll look into it and let you know.

98
00:05:47,994 --> 00:05:49,079
Hold on.

99
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:51,790
Oh my gosh.

100
00:05:52,290 --> 00:05:53,416
What?

101
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:55,835
They're doing a CT, an MRI,
and even drawing blood?

102
00:05:56,962 --> 00:05:58,088
Blood?

103
00:05:58,171 --> 00:05:59,422
You cannot have my blood!

104
00:05:59,506 --> 00:06:01,424
Who knows what you will use it for?

105
00:06:01,967 --> 00:06:03,843
We'll use it for your health checkup.

106
00:06:05,804 --> 00:06:07,097
She is something else.

107
00:06:08,223 --> 00:06:10,684
We just had the first-class passengers
sign notarized NDAs,

108
00:06:10,767 --> 00:06:12,394
and their compensation
has been paid out.

109
00:06:12,477 --> 00:06:14,980
Good thing weekday flights are quiet.
We're bleeding money.

110
00:06:15,063 --> 00:06:17,148
Sir, you should request
a proper police investigation.

111
00:06:17,232 --> 00:06:18,900
It's not just rumors anymore.

112
00:06:18,984 --> 00:06:21,277
They bribed a nurse to drug you this time.

113
00:06:21,361 --> 00:06:22,612
You were in real danger.

114
00:06:22,696 --> 00:06:24,239
For someone in my position,

115
00:06:24,322 --> 00:06:26,199
this kind of threat is all too common.

116
00:06:26,282 --> 00:06:28,410
I can't be terrified every time.

117
00:06:28,493 --> 00:06:30,286
The moment I show my fear,

118
00:06:30,370 --> 00:06:31,579
it's game over for me.

119
00:06:31,663 --> 00:06:33,206
Even so, some people need to know.

120
00:06:33,289 --> 00:06:35,041
Hiding this even from your doctor friend--

121
00:06:35,125 --> 00:06:36,626
Isn't that a given?

122
00:06:36,710 --> 00:06:38,169
He could've been bought off.

123
00:06:38,253 --> 00:06:39,212
Lead with suspicion.

124
00:06:39,295 --> 00:06:40,463
By that logic,

125
00:06:41,047 --> 00:06:43,466
isn't Ms. Shin Seo-ri the most suspicious?

126
00:06:44,300 --> 00:06:45,760
Shin Seo-ri?

127
00:06:47,429 --> 00:06:48,930
-What about her?
-Just think about it.

128
00:06:49,014 --> 00:06:51,933
You two met over a fender bender,
then came an assault, investor problems,

129
00:06:52,017 --> 00:06:54,477
a police summons,
and now corporate shakedown rumors.

130
00:06:54,561 --> 00:06:57,522
It looks like she straight-up brought
calamity into your life.

131
00:06:57,605 --> 00:06:58,982
I'll give you the fender bender,

132
00:06:59,065 --> 00:07:01,818
but the rest has
absolutely nothing to do with her.

133
00:07:02,444 --> 00:07:03,862
Mr. Son.

134
00:07:03,945 --> 00:07:04,946
Yes, sir.

135
00:07:05,030 --> 00:07:07,866
You are an executive aide.
Your job is to deliver the facts.

136
00:07:08,616 --> 00:07:09,784
Yes, sir.

137
00:07:10,660 --> 00:07:11,619
Sir.

138
00:07:16,458 --> 00:07:18,835
I guess I'm just the big old jerk
in this scenario.

139
00:07:18,918 --> 00:07:20,128
Unbelievable.

140
00:07:20,211 --> 00:07:22,797
What a stand-up guy he is.

141
00:07:23,381 --> 00:07:25,884
They said there's
nothing seriously wrong with her.

142
00:07:25,967 --> 00:07:27,802
She's good to go after an IV drip.

143
00:07:27,886 --> 00:07:29,804
<i>Must have been quite the shock</i>
<i>on your first day.</i>

144
00:07:29,888 --> 00:07:31,347
<i>It's Gwang-nam, right?</i>

145
00:07:31,431 --> 00:07:34,768
I heard you two are close, like siblings.
Please take good care of her.

146
00:07:34,851 --> 00:07:37,020
<i>I'll head down</i>
<i>after my meetings in Seoul.</i>

147
00:07:37,103 --> 00:07:39,230
I think there's been
a huge misunderstanding,

148
00:07:39,314 --> 00:07:40,815
so let me clear it up right now.

149
00:07:40,899 --> 00:07:42,317
We are not like siblings at all.

150
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:43,902
It's strictly business between us.

151
00:07:43,985 --> 00:07:45,236
And I'm not staying long.

152
00:07:45,320 --> 00:07:47,363
It's just a temp job
until I get a real one.

153
00:07:47,447 --> 00:07:50,158
You should start looking
for a replacement right away.

154
00:07:53,620 --> 00:07:54,788
Damn it.

155
00:07:56,498 --> 00:07:59,667
Leave it to her
to hire someone exactly like her.

156
00:07:59,751 --> 00:08:01,252
Why? What did her manager say?

157
00:08:01,336 --> 00:08:04,255
He said he's just a temp
and told me to replace him.

158
00:08:04,339 --> 00:08:06,549
He's really drawing
a bold line in the sand.

159
00:08:06,633 --> 00:08:07,967
Birds of a feather flock together.

160
00:08:08,051 --> 00:08:10,011
Can you blame him?

161
00:08:10,095 --> 00:08:11,679
Look at who he works for.

162
00:08:11,755 --> 00:08:13,882
I wondered why the pushover
suddenly grew a spine.

163
00:08:13,980 --> 00:08:15,809
Turns out there was a good reason.

164
00:08:15,892 --> 00:08:17,268
What reason?

165
00:08:18,186 --> 00:08:19,687
It looked like

166
00:08:19,771 --> 00:08:22,023
that loser hooked a rich boyfriend.

167
00:08:22,107 --> 00:08:24,400
Although I'm not sure if he's
a boyfriend or a sugar daddy.

168
00:08:25,735 --> 00:08:26,611
Okay.

169
00:08:28,321 --> 00:08:30,824
You're good to proceed
with the ad campaign now.

170
00:08:30,907 --> 00:08:31,825
I'm off.

171
00:08:36,412 --> 00:08:38,456
What blind idiot would go for her?

172
00:08:38,540 --> 00:08:40,250
My ideal type?

173
00:08:40,333 --> 00:08:43,837
<i>A man like Hugh Grant in </i>Notting Hill.

174
00:08:43,920 --> 00:08:46,798
<i>He's practically every woman's dream.</i>

175
00:08:46,881 --> 00:08:49,717
Yoon Ji-hyo's manager is so lucky.

176
00:08:49,801 --> 00:08:52,178
He gets paid to go
to a free fan meeting every day.

177
00:08:53,096 --> 00:08:55,557
If I were her manager,
I'd totally work for free.

178
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:57,684
They'll all recognize you in Jeju.

179
00:08:57,767 --> 00:09:00,395
Maybe I could look into flights
to Taiwan or Japan

180
00:09:00,478 --> 00:09:02,313
that leave today instead?

181
00:09:02,397 --> 00:09:04,149
Everyone <i>will</i> recognize you in Jeju.

182
00:09:04,232 --> 00:09:07,193
Taiwan is where that jerk Gong Tae-woo
and I celebrated our first anniversary.

183
00:09:07,277 --> 00:09:10,655
Japan is where we had
that Christmas birthday event.

184
00:09:11,823 --> 00:09:12,699
Don't worry.

185
00:09:12,782 --> 00:09:16,035
I rented out
an entire private resort anyway.

186
00:09:16,536 --> 00:09:18,413
I won't be running into anyone there.

187
00:09:18,496 --> 00:09:21,708
HALLA GENERAL HOSPITAL

188
00:09:32,510 --> 00:09:33,928
Listen here.

189
00:09:34,012 --> 00:09:35,930
Where is the one named Cha Se-gye?

190
00:09:36,014 --> 00:09:37,182
How can I help you?

191
00:09:37,265 --> 00:09:38,850
I have come to see him.

192
00:09:38,933 --> 00:09:40,059
Lead the way.

193
00:09:40,935 --> 00:09:42,145
What's with her tone…

194
00:09:43,146 --> 00:09:45,690
Miss, may I have your name first?

195
00:09:45,773 --> 00:09:46,733
Why do you need my name?

196
00:09:48,193 --> 00:09:50,236
I don't think you should be
wandering alone just yet.

197
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,654
Don't go anywhere.

198
00:09:51,738 --> 00:09:53,031
Just stay put for now.

199
00:09:53,114 --> 00:09:54,073
How dare you!

200
00:09:54,616 --> 00:09:56,367
You have yet to answer my question.

201
00:09:57,368 --> 00:09:59,078
Is this the psych ward?

202
00:10:00,079 --> 00:10:03,249
-Listen here, I have a question.
-Yes?

203
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:06,002
Do you know where the one named
Cha Se-gye is convalescing?

204
00:10:06,085 --> 00:10:07,587
Pardon me? "Convalescing"?

205
00:10:07,670 --> 00:10:10,757
Miss, do you happen to remember
which room you're in?

206
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:13,801
Is giving nonsensical answers
the physicians' specialty at this clinic?

207
00:10:13,885 --> 00:10:15,929
Everybody refuses to answer my questions.

208
00:10:16,012 --> 00:10:18,056
Just stay right here.

209
00:10:19,265 --> 00:10:22,143
Why do you all keep telling me
to stay still like a sack of grain!

210
00:10:22,227 --> 00:10:23,311
Shin Seo-ri.

211
00:10:34,614 --> 00:10:37,951
The media response to the groundbreaking
of Songjin Resort has been positive.

212
00:10:38,034 --> 00:10:39,911
Let's wrap up
the foundation work this year.

213
00:10:39,994 --> 00:10:41,454
Once it's completed in 2029,

214
00:10:41,537 --> 00:10:44,749
I trust Chail Food will handle
the F&amp;B operations well.

215
00:10:44,832 --> 00:10:47,669
Thanks to that, we're finally seeing
some green after a long time.

216
00:10:47,752 --> 00:10:49,504
The shareholders are very pleased.

217
00:10:49,587 --> 00:10:51,047
Thanks to Mun-do,

218
00:10:51,130 --> 00:10:53,591
you can finally hold your head up
in front of your shareholders.

219
00:10:53,675 --> 00:10:56,302
Ever since the accounting fraud
sent their stock tanking,

220
00:10:56,386 --> 00:10:57,887
they've been absolutely miserable.

221
00:10:57,971 --> 00:10:59,347
Without even lifting a finger.

222
00:10:59,430 --> 00:11:01,140
It's a total win-win.

223
00:11:07,730 --> 00:11:10,566
CHA SE-GYE FAINTS ON FLIGHT TO JEJU
RECOVERING IN JEJU HOSPITAL

224
00:11:21,619 --> 00:11:22,662
Are you truly all right?

225
00:11:22,745 --> 00:11:24,872
Stop fussing. You're giving me a headache.

226
00:11:25,415 --> 00:11:28,459
You must truly be okay after all
if you're still able to be this cranky.

227
00:11:28,543 --> 00:11:30,878
I'm not okay at all, you clueless woman.

228
00:11:30,962 --> 00:11:32,463
Why not just stay out of the way?

229
00:11:32,547 --> 00:11:34,590
I very nearly died thanks to you.

230
00:11:34,674 --> 00:11:36,551
People do not die that easily.

231
00:11:36,634 --> 00:11:39,220
I speak from extensive experience
with near-death events.

232
00:11:39,304 --> 00:11:41,848
The thread of life is
surprisingly tough, like steel.

233
00:11:41,931 --> 00:11:44,809
Unless your time has come,
it does not snap easily.

234
00:11:44,892 --> 00:11:46,644
Spare me the cheap philosophy.

235
00:11:46,728 --> 00:11:48,146
Why are you here?

236
00:11:49,022 --> 00:11:50,148
I am not here for you.

237
00:11:51,524 --> 00:11:52,942
I was just passing through.

238
00:11:53,026 --> 00:11:54,986
The VIP ward is nowhere
near the first-floor ER.

239
00:11:55,069 --> 00:11:57,405
There's no way
you were just passing through.

240
00:12:02,994 --> 00:12:05,330
Looks like you were
pretty worried about me.

241
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:07,373
Worried?

242
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:11,210
Of course I was worried.

243
00:12:11,294 --> 00:12:12,545
If the money man goes down,

244
00:12:12,628 --> 00:12:14,255
my prospects naturally go down with him.

245
00:12:14,339 --> 00:12:15,798
I had no choice but to worry.

246
00:12:16,341 --> 00:12:19,177
That's enough.
Spare me your capitalist concerns.

247
00:12:19,844 --> 00:12:21,763
There you are, Mr. Cha.

248
00:12:21,846 --> 00:12:25,433
We've forwarded the detailed results
to your primary physician,

249
00:12:25,516 --> 00:12:27,518
so you may be discharged immediately
as requested.

250
00:12:27,602 --> 00:12:28,644
Thank you.

251
00:12:28,728 --> 00:12:30,480
And regarding that patient

252
00:12:30,563 --> 00:12:32,565
you asked about earlier…

253
00:12:32,648 --> 00:12:34,400
Hold on. You go in here for a second.

254
00:12:34,484 --> 00:12:35,443
Why?

255
00:12:35,526 --> 00:12:37,612
Don't argue. Just go.

256
00:12:40,156 --> 00:12:41,866
-Please continue.
-According to the results,

257
00:12:41,949 --> 00:12:44,327
Ms. Shin Seo-ri has
no major health issues.

258
00:12:45,286 --> 00:12:46,454
Nothing to worry about.

259
00:12:47,330 --> 00:12:48,748
-I see.
-Yes. Take care.

260
00:12:56,506 --> 00:12:57,965
Goodness me.

261
00:13:01,969 --> 00:13:05,056
That flying palanquin was split
into beggar and commoner sections.

262
00:13:05,139 --> 00:13:07,350
It seems this clinic is no different.

263
00:13:09,936 --> 00:13:12,188
My goodness. It is so big.

264
00:13:12,271 --> 00:13:14,399
FOR A FLIRTY MOOD

265
00:13:17,610 --> 00:13:18,569
There.

266
00:13:21,572 --> 00:13:22,448
Cha Se-gye.

267
00:13:22,532 --> 00:13:25,368
I thought your complexion
had gone from deathly to radiant.

268
00:13:25,451 --> 00:13:27,537
-Now I see why.
-What is it now?

269
00:13:28,204 --> 00:13:30,039
This room is an absolute palace.

270
00:13:30,706 --> 00:13:31,582
We're both patients,

271
00:13:31,666 --> 00:13:34,252
yet they have me cooped up in a shoebox.

272
00:13:34,335 --> 00:13:35,878
This room has everything.

273
00:13:35,962 --> 00:13:37,839
Did you think we were on the same level?

274
00:13:37,922 --> 00:13:40,049
Just look at the size of that TV.

275
00:13:41,050 --> 00:13:42,927
And the sound quality is superb!

276
00:13:43,010 --> 00:13:45,346
Hey, that's too loud. Turn it down.

277
00:13:45,430 --> 00:13:47,223
Let me enjoy this palace too!

278
00:13:47,306 --> 00:13:49,350
-Not a chance.
-Hand it over, now!

279
00:13:49,434 --> 00:13:50,935
Try to take it.

280
00:13:52,353 --> 00:13:53,855
-What's wrong with you?
-Come on!

281
00:13:55,273 --> 00:13:56,816
Don't use force. Hey, wait a minute.

282
00:13:56,899 --> 00:13:58,359
We're going to fall. Hold on…

283
00:14:00,445 --> 00:14:01,362
Hey.

284
00:14:01,446 --> 00:14:03,406
-Let me watch some TV too!
-Hey!

285
00:14:04,073 --> 00:14:05,283
Stop that.

286
00:14:05,366 --> 00:14:06,784
Hey!

287
00:14:27,305 --> 00:14:29,223
WARMTH OF THE CANOLA FLOWER FIELD

288
00:14:34,937 --> 00:14:36,272
Oh my.

289
00:14:36,355 --> 00:14:39,150
I think I have the wrong room…

290
00:14:39,233 --> 00:14:41,194
No, I just have terrible timing.

291
00:14:48,034 --> 00:14:49,076
No.

292
00:14:50,161 --> 00:14:51,412
It's not what it looks like.

293
00:14:51,496 --> 00:14:53,456
I definitely knocked,

294
00:14:53,539 --> 00:14:54,582
but not hard enough.

295
00:14:54,665 --> 00:14:57,210
Since you hate loud noises so much,

296
00:14:57,293 --> 00:14:59,712
I just knocked lightly like I always do.

297
00:14:59,795 --> 00:15:02,048
If I had known a lady…
I mean, Ms. Shin Seo-ri was here,

298
00:15:02,131 --> 00:15:04,967
I should've knocked harder. Darn it.

299
00:15:05,051 --> 00:15:07,220
What are you talking about?

300
00:15:07,845 --> 00:15:10,181
This was… just an accident.

301
00:15:11,474 --> 00:15:13,809
It was like… a car accident.

302
00:15:13,893 --> 00:15:15,186
Yes… Right.

303
00:15:15,853 --> 00:15:17,897
As the old proverb goes,

304
00:15:17,980 --> 00:15:19,148
"Do not take your shoes off

305
00:15:19,232 --> 00:15:22,151
in a cucumber patch, and do not adjust
your hat string under a pear tree."

306
00:15:22,235 --> 00:15:24,946
It looks suspicious
to any onlooker, but this is…

307
00:15:25,029 --> 00:15:25,988
just a coincidence.

308
00:15:27,323 --> 00:15:30,284
Save the rambling explanation.
You're just making it weirder.

309
00:15:30,368 --> 00:15:31,786
Was I?

310
00:15:31,869 --> 00:15:33,079
I was trying my best.

311
00:15:33,162 --> 00:15:34,288
I'll come back later.

312
00:15:34,372 --> 00:15:36,123
-Don't go!
-Freeze!

313
00:15:46,676 --> 00:15:47,802
Damn it.

314
00:15:49,095 --> 00:15:50,805
That nearly scared me to death.

315
00:15:50,888 --> 00:15:53,057
That wicked creature.

316
00:15:55,977 --> 00:15:56,894
Is it all done?

317
00:15:56,978 --> 00:15:59,230
I made sure to keep
the passengers quiet.

318
00:15:59,313 --> 00:16:00,815
And your discharge is all sorted.

319
00:16:00,898 --> 00:16:02,066
Good work.

320
00:16:04,193 --> 00:16:06,612
I'll get changed and head out,
so be on standby.

321
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:09,115
Sir, don't you think
you should stay a day

322
00:16:09,198 --> 00:16:11,033
and see how you feel?

323
00:16:11,117 --> 00:16:12,493
My test results are fine.

324
00:16:12,994 --> 00:16:15,496
Even if they weren't,
discharge is unavoidable.

325
00:16:15,580 --> 00:16:17,331
If we throw
health scare rumors into the mix,

326
00:16:17,415 --> 00:16:20,585
investors will demand
their money back before the launch.

327
00:16:22,503 --> 00:16:23,754
That's true.

328
00:16:24,380 --> 00:16:25,923
What about the other thing?

329
00:16:26,007 --> 00:16:28,884
After the shareholders' meeting,
President Choi is carrying out

330
00:16:28,968 --> 00:16:31,012
his schedule as planned.

331
00:16:31,637 --> 00:16:34,056
He must've been briefed
on my condition by now.

332
00:16:35,057 --> 00:16:36,017
Perfectly healthy.

333
00:16:36,100 --> 00:16:37,226
So,

334
00:16:38,019 --> 00:16:40,146
you really think
President Choi is behind this?

335
00:16:40,229 --> 00:16:42,064
Who else has the guts

336
00:16:42,148 --> 00:16:44,150
to pull off something like this?

337
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:47,695
The deepfake,

338
00:16:48,362 --> 00:16:50,573
<i>the attack, the rumors…</i>

339
00:16:50,656 --> 00:16:53,409
<i>And most importantly,</i>
<i>the Kaiserman private equity fund.</i>

340
00:16:53,492 --> 00:16:54,910
All evidence points to him.

341
00:16:54,994 --> 00:16:57,204
He doesn't even seem to be hiding it.

342
00:16:57,288 --> 00:16:59,290
I'm not sure if he's just confident…

343
00:17:02,209 --> 00:17:03,753
or if he has a massive ego.

344
00:17:12,678 --> 00:17:14,055
Good work, everyone.

345
00:17:26,901 --> 00:17:29,070
Mr. Cha had the airline
and all the passengers

346
00:17:29,153 --> 00:17:30,946
sign notarized NDAs.

347
00:17:31,030 --> 00:17:33,074
Should we offer to pay the penalty
if they talk to us?

348
00:17:33,157 --> 00:17:34,742
Just make contact for now.

349
00:17:34,825 --> 00:17:36,452
We don't want needless chatter

350
00:17:36,535 --> 00:17:38,079
tanking the group's stock.

351
00:17:38,162 --> 00:17:39,497
Block any related articles.

352
00:17:40,247 --> 00:17:41,874
-For now.
-Just for now?

353
00:17:41,957 --> 00:17:44,335
Cha Se-gye must know by now.

354
00:17:44,919 --> 00:17:47,546
How far I'm willing to go for Chail

355
00:17:47,630 --> 00:17:49,131
and what I'm aiming for.

356
00:17:50,466 --> 00:17:51,967
It's a mental game from here on out.

357
00:17:52,051 --> 00:17:53,886
Whoever backs down first loses.

358
00:18:12,446 --> 00:18:14,699
-You really haven't seen her?
-I haven't.

359
00:18:15,616 --> 00:18:18,160
Where did she go?
I'm about to lose it.

360
00:18:18,786 --> 00:18:21,914
Hey, where did you go without telling me?

361
00:18:21,997 --> 00:18:24,583
Must I report my every move to you?

362
00:18:25,126 --> 00:18:26,794
When a master leaves the premises,

363
00:18:26,877 --> 00:18:29,922
it is the servant's duty
to wait quietly for her return.

364
00:18:30,005 --> 00:18:32,341
You still need to tell me,
so I don't worry.

365
00:18:32,425 --> 00:18:34,844
You were worried
about your money, not me.

366
00:18:35,928 --> 00:18:37,805
Cease your fretting and prepare to leave.

367
00:18:37,888 --> 00:18:39,598
You know our destination, yes?

368
00:18:39,682 --> 00:18:40,558
Discharging already?

369
00:18:40,641 --> 00:18:42,476
I have secured an iron palanquin for us,

370
00:18:42,560 --> 00:18:43,686
so come along.

371
00:18:44,311 --> 00:18:45,229
Iron palanquin?

372
00:18:52,403 --> 00:18:54,238
Mr. Son, what exactly is going on here?

373
00:18:54,321 --> 00:18:57,366
Well, the ad agency must have
booked the whole place.

374
00:18:57,450 --> 00:18:59,577
Turns out they're staying
at the same resort.

375
00:18:59,660 --> 00:19:01,162
They asked for a ride.

376
00:19:01,245 --> 00:19:02,955
This isn't an airport shuttle.

377
00:19:03,038 --> 00:19:05,374
You can't just let anyone ride with us.

378
00:19:05,458 --> 00:19:07,251
Must you be so unyielding?

379
00:19:07,918 --> 00:19:09,795
We can keep you company
on this lonely journey

380
00:19:09,879 --> 00:19:11,422
and fill these empty seats.

381
00:19:11,505 --> 00:19:12,840
Kill two birds with one stone.

382
00:19:12,923 --> 00:19:14,508
I never asked for company.

383
00:19:14,592 --> 00:19:17,803
We should've just rented a car
to avoid this being so awkward.

384
00:19:17,887 --> 00:19:19,847
I do not trust
your palanquin-driving skills,

385
00:19:19,930 --> 00:19:21,223
so hold your tongue.

386
00:19:21,891 --> 00:19:23,100
I'm sorry to interrupt,

387
00:19:23,184 --> 00:19:25,269
but can we stop at a rest area?

388
00:19:25,352 --> 00:19:27,104
Already? It hasn't even been five minutes.

389
00:19:27,188 --> 00:19:29,356
Well, I drank a latte on the plane,

390
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:32,818
and it's making my stomach
rumble like crazy.

391
00:19:32,902 --> 00:19:34,987
You're lactose intolerant.

392
00:19:35,070 --> 00:19:36,781
Why would you drink a latte?

393
00:19:37,615 --> 00:19:38,491
Oh man.

394
00:19:38,574 --> 00:19:41,118
-Lactose intolerance?
<i>-Wait, could this be…</i>

395
00:19:41,202 --> 00:19:43,037
If we throw
health scare rumors into the mix,

396
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:45,956
investors will demand
their money back before the launch.

397
00:19:46,499 --> 00:19:47,374
"Health scare"?

398
00:19:48,042 --> 00:19:50,294
<i>One collapses backward,</i>

399
00:19:50,377 --> 00:19:52,129
<i>and the other's stomach is rumbling.</i>

400
00:19:52,213 --> 00:19:55,591
<i>Chest pain, fainting,</i>
<i>and now dysentery too.</i>

401
00:19:55,674 --> 00:19:56,884
<i>These sound like the symptoms…</i>

402
00:19:56,967 --> 00:19:58,636
Could it be a plague?

403
00:19:58,719 --> 00:20:01,180
Halt this iron palanquin.
Stop the car right now!

404
00:20:01,263 --> 00:20:02,223
What's wrong now?

405
00:20:02,306 --> 00:20:03,307
-Seo-ri.
-Are you carsick?

406
00:20:03,390 --> 00:20:05,184
I am going to get out now.
Stop the car at once!

407
00:20:05,267 --> 00:20:06,769
-No! Please…
-We can't just stop

408
00:20:06,852 --> 00:20:08,270
in the middle of the road. Just wait.

409
00:20:08,354 --> 00:20:10,773
The plague is far worse
than any tiger or smallpox!

410
00:20:10,868 --> 00:20:12,691
This is tantamount to suicide!

411
00:20:12,775 --> 00:20:14,026
Manager Baek! Open the door!

412
00:20:14,109 --> 00:20:15,027
-Okay.
-Open the door!

413
00:20:15,110 --> 00:20:16,320
-Don't open it.
-Someone help!

414
00:20:16,403 --> 00:20:18,405
Help! It is the plague! The plague!

415
00:20:18,489 --> 00:20:19,782
Someone help me!

416
00:20:22,743 --> 00:20:23,744
It is the plague!

417
00:20:25,663 --> 00:20:27,081
Did you really just throw a fit

418
00:20:27,164 --> 00:20:29,291
in the middle of the road
to save yourself?

419
00:20:29,834 --> 00:20:31,710
I had no other choice.

420
00:20:32,711 --> 00:20:36,090
If not poison, the symptoms matched
the plague perfectly.

421
00:20:36,173 --> 00:20:37,466
What else was I supposed to do?

422
00:20:37,550 --> 00:20:39,134
You hitched a ride, offering "company,"

423
00:20:39,218 --> 00:20:41,470
but I guess a plague changes everything.

424
00:20:41,554 --> 00:20:43,264
You do not know
the true terror of a plague.

425
00:20:43,347 --> 00:20:45,808
Once infected, it spares no one,

426
00:20:45,891 --> 00:20:47,059
be it a king or a commoner.

427
00:20:53,524 --> 00:20:57,903
I see now. So is that why
you maintain such a great distance?

428
00:20:57,987 --> 00:20:59,947
"Hope for the best,
prepare for the worst."

429
00:21:00,030 --> 00:21:02,908
It is always best
to be prepared for anything.

430
00:21:03,659 --> 00:21:06,871
From now on,
I shall do nothing but breathe.

431
00:21:07,580 --> 00:21:10,332
Think of me as a sack of barley,
and pay me no mind.

432
00:21:10,875 --> 00:21:14,128
A plague fighter to a sack of barley.
One hell of a switch in attitude.

433
00:21:15,170 --> 00:21:18,173
Sir, we should get going.
The sun is setting.

434
00:21:18,674 --> 00:21:22,052
For dysentery of unknown cause,
cranesbill is a surefire remedy.

435
00:21:22,136 --> 00:21:24,138
Cranesbill petals have three stripes,

436
00:21:24,221 --> 00:21:25,264
while geraniums have five.

437
00:21:25,347 --> 00:21:26,974
Do not confuse them.

438
00:21:27,057 --> 00:21:28,726
Look at our Joseon-era doctor over here.

439
00:21:28,809 --> 00:21:32,479
Your meddling stretches
as far as the Great Wall.

440
00:21:33,105 --> 00:21:35,190
Why are you nitpicking
every little thing today?

441
00:21:35,274 --> 00:21:38,277
Just because I rejected your affections,
you hound me all damn day?

442
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:39,278
Oh my goodness.

443
00:21:39,361 --> 00:21:40,821
What do you think you're doing?

444
00:21:40,905 --> 00:21:43,616
Are you trying to broadcast
your rejection of me to the whole world?

445
00:21:43,699 --> 00:21:44,700
Jeez.

446
00:21:45,284 --> 00:21:46,619
You'd better stop.

447
00:21:46,702 --> 00:21:47,578
Let's go.

448
00:21:48,078 --> 00:21:49,079
Get in, hurry.

449
00:21:55,252 --> 00:21:57,296
It might look like nothing special,

450
00:21:57,379 --> 00:21:58,923
but this tree is a handful to maintain.

451
00:21:59,006 --> 00:22:00,090
-You see…
-Father?

452
00:22:00,174 --> 00:22:01,050
Hey.

453
00:22:01,133 --> 00:22:02,426
Hello.

454
00:22:02,509 --> 00:22:03,844
I'm Mo Tae-hee.

455
00:22:03,928 --> 00:22:05,554
She went on a blind date with Se-gye.

456
00:22:05,638 --> 00:22:07,431
The third daughter of the Mochang Group.

457
00:22:08,390 --> 00:22:10,601
-Is that so?
-You must be the second aunt.

458
00:22:10,684 --> 00:22:14,313
Thanks to you, Mochang Woolen
is forever stuck in second place.

459
00:22:14,396 --> 00:22:16,440
Well, latecomers don't have
much of a choice.

460
00:22:16,523 --> 00:22:18,984
Father, did you hear about Se-gye?

461
00:22:19,526 --> 00:22:20,611
Yes.

462
00:22:20,694 --> 00:22:22,821
I was so shocked on my way here.

463
00:22:23,530 --> 00:22:25,574
So, I was thinking we should
ask outsiders to leave

464
00:22:25,658 --> 00:22:27,284
and talk among ourselves.

465
00:22:27,368 --> 00:22:29,036
I heard the news too.

466
00:22:29,119 --> 00:22:31,330
A small incident on the plane.

467
00:22:31,413 --> 00:22:32,831
-An incident?
-Yes.

468
00:22:32,915 --> 00:22:36,043
Fortunately, they handled it quickly
and resumed their schedule.

469
00:22:36,126 --> 00:22:37,086
Se-gye said that?

470
00:22:37,169 --> 00:22:39,088
I was surprised too,

471
00:22:39,171 --> 00:22:42,675
but she came by to reassure me
that it was nothing to worry about.

472
00:22:42,758 --> 00:22:45,010
You must have been
very worried about Se-gye.

473
00:22:45,094 --> 00:22:46,512
Seeing how you rushed right over.

474
00:22:46,595 --> 00:22:49,556
I thought he'd be lonely
growing up without a mother,

475
00:22:49,640 --> 00:22:51,850
but he's lucky to have an aunt like you.

476
00:22:53,602 --> 00:22:54,520
Yes.

477
00:22:54,603 --> 00:22:56,814
I have cleaned up a lot of his messes.

478
00:22:58,399 --> 00:22:59,483
What's this?

479
00:22:59,566 --> 00:23:01,110
I thought you went home.

480
00:23:01,652 --> 00:23:03,612
Hello. You must be the eldest aunt.

481
00:23:03,696 --> 00:23:05,030
It's a pleasure to meet you.

482
00:23:05,114 --> 00:23:06,198
I'm Mo Tae-hee.

483
00:23:06,281 --> 00:23:07,741
Okay. Nice to meet you.

484
00:23:12,579 --> 00:23:14,248
May I visit again?

485
00:23:14,331 --> 00:23:15,791
You both seem so lovely.

486
00:23:15,874 --> 00:23:17,668
I'd love to see you more often.

487
00:23:30,222 --> 00:23:31,557
<i>Visiting Jeju Island for work.</i>

488
00:23:31,640 --> 00:23:33,017
<i>Even the sky welcomes me.</i>

489
00:23:33,642 --> 00:23:35,561
<i>Should I report this or not?</i>

490
00:23:42,693 --> 00:23:44,987
The road is quite bumpy. Hold on tight.

491
00:23:49,450 --> 00:23:52,119
She's actually shut up.
Finally, some peace and quiet.

492
00:23:56,874 --> 00:23:59,668
<i>Threatened by an assassin</i>
<i>in broad daylight.</i>

493
00:23:59,752 --> 00:24:01,587
Why are you sprawled out like this?

494
00:24:01,670 --> 00:24:04,089
<i>And he just collapsed,</i>
<i>despite being in perfect health.</i>

495
00:24:09,678 --> 00:24:10,554
Mr. Son.

496
00:24:10,637 --> 00:24:12,264
Try to drive more carefully.

497
00:24:14,224 --> 00:24:15,225
Gosh.

498
00:24:15,893 --> 00:24:17,478
Come on now.

499
00:24:21,273 --> 00:24:22,149
<i>Ms. Shin.</i>

500
00:24:22,232 --> 00:24:24,151
You should be friends with Cha Se-gye.

501
00:24:24,735 --> 00:24:28,322
<i>Is that man wearing the king's face</i>
<i>the poisonous influence in your life,</i>

502
00:24:28,405 --> 00:24:29,615
<i>not mine?</i>

503
00:24:29,698 --> 00:24:31,784
<i>Your luck with people rivals mine.</i>

504
00:24:33,243 --> 00:24:35,412
Jesus, you startled me.
What are you staring at?

505
00:24:35,496 --> 00:24:38,540
Are you absolutely certain
you didn't swallow poison?

506
00:24:39,416 --> 00:24:42,086
Who's being poisoned in the 21st century?

507
00:24:43,087 --> 00:24:45,464
If it isn't a plague or poison,

508
00:24:45,547 --> 00:24:47,007
how does a healthy man--

509
00:24:47,091 --> 00:24:48,884
It's just chronic fatigue. So what?

510
00:24:50,385 --> 00:24:52,554
What good is a man so frail?

511
00:24:52,638 --> 00:24:54,556
Who are you calling frail? I'm…

512
00:24:56,850 --> 00:24:59,144
You have no idea
how much I can squat.

513
00:24:59,228 --> 00:25:01,021
You are all talk.

514
00:25:01,605 --> 00:25:03,023
Look. The ocean.

515
00:25:12,366 --> 00:25:14,493
Well, Mr. Cha's office

516
00:25:14,576 --> 00:25:16,870
won't stop calling me.

517
00:25:16,954 --> 00:25:18,956
I can't keep pretending I'm not home.

518
00:25:19,039 --> 00:25:20,124
When can I stop hiding?

519
00:25:20,207 --> 00:25:22,584
<i>There are no cameras in the lab.</i>

520
00:25:22,668 --> 00:25:24,920
<i>They can't do anything</i>
<i>with just suspicions.</i>

521
00:25:25,003 --> 00:25:26,839
They have no proof.

522
00:25:34,263 --> 00:25:36,682
And there's no way
they can trace the accounts.

523
00:25:39,476 --> 00:25:41,311
Go overseas for a while.

524
00:25:43,188 --> 00:25:46,233
I'll have a place ready for you
when things quiet down.

525
00:25:50,362 --> 00:25:52,072
Thank you.

526
00:25:56,618 --> 00:25:58,996
What should we do?
She looks very anxious.

527
00:25:59,955 --> 00:26:02,499
Wait for the right time
to take care of her quietly.

528
00:26:04,793 --> 00:26:06,920
The world truly has changed.

529
00:26:07,004 --> 00:26:09,006
This island of Tamna was infamous

530
00:26:09,089 --> 00:26:11,633
as a desolate place of exile,
reserved only for the worst traitors

531
00:26:11,717 --> 00:26:13,468
who plotted treason against the throne.

532
00:26:14,303 --> 00:26:16,180
How does <i>this</i> look like an exile site?

533
00:26:16,263 --> 00:26:17,556
It's a paradise resort.

534
00:26:17,639 --> 00:26:20,434
Jeju is too crowded now
to even be a resort.

535
00:26:20,517 --> 00:26:23,812
Maybe some deserted Pacific island
might come close to a retreat.

536
00:26:23,896 --> 00:26:24,855
Yeah.

537
00:26:25,439 --> 00:26:27,649
You might actually get
some rest somewhere like that.

538
00:26:27,733 --> 00:26:29,693
It gives off Mont Saint-Michel vibes.

539
00:26:31,445 --> 00:26:33,030
What? "Monsoon Seashell"?

540
00:26:34,489 --> 00:26:37,284
It's a rocky island
off the coast of Normandy, France.

541
00:26:37,367 --> 00:26:40,120
Is that Mont-whatever
a deserted island too?

542
00:26:40,204 --> 00:26:42,873
No, it only becomes
an island at high tide.

543
00:26:42,956 --> 00:26:43,957
It's pretty nice.

544
00:26:44,041 --> 00:26:46,043
If my new launch is a huge hit,

545
00:26:46,126 --> 00:26:47,794
I'm thinking of buying an island.

546
00:26:48,962 --> 00:26:51,089
A private island retreat
sounds nice, doesn't it?

547
00:26:51,173 --> 00:26:53,133
Forget about your Monsoon Seashells.

548
00:26:53,217 --> 00:26:55,302
I think Tamna is pretty nice already.

549
00:26:55,385 --> 00:26:57,221
Actually, I like it very much.

550
00:26:58,305 --> 00:27:00,140
First time in Jeju?

551
00:27:00,224 --> 00:27:02,142
-Bring it down a notch.
-It is my first time.

552
00:27:02,226 --> 00:27:04,311
It is my first time seeing the ocean.

553
00:27:08,440 --> 00:27:11,443
You live in a country surrounded
by water on three sides,

554
00:27:11,526 --> 00:27:12,945
and this is your first time?

555
00:27:15,405 --> 00:27:16,740
Cha Se-gye.

556
00:27:16,823 --> 00:27:18,700
You should try taking in
a deep breath too.

557
00:27:31,421 --> 00:27:34,091
If I had died without witnessing
this wonderful sight…

558
00:27:36,134 --> 00:27:37,719
it would have been my greatest regret.

559
00:27:59,449 --> 00:28:04,162
SEOGEON ISLAND
JEJU'S ISLAND OF MYSTERY

560
00:28:07,833 --> 00:28:11,044
<i>Korea's very own Miracle of Moses.</i>
<i>The Seogeon Island Sea Parting.</i>

561
00:28:12,462 --> 00:28:14,256
<i>When you need to take a break.</i>

562
00:28:14,923 --> 00:28:17,592
<i>Are you on vacation too?</i>
<i>It's like we read each other's minds.</i>

563
00:28:17,676 --> 00:28:19,511
<i>Korea is full of amazing places.</i>

564
00:28:19,594 --> 00:28:21,054
<i>The sea parts at low tide.</i>

565
00:28:21,596 --> 00:28:24,016
<i>Maybe the Miracle of Moses</i>
<i>was just low tide.</i>

566
00:28:51,376 --> 00:28:52,294
Gosh.

567
00:29:02,971 --> 00:29:03,930
Wait.

568
00:29:04,514 --> 00:29:05,766
There are brine stones here.

569
00:29:05,849 --> 00:29:07,726
-"Brine stone"?
-Brine stone.

570
00:29:08,310 --> 00:29:09,394
As in "pebble."

571
00:29:10,103 --> 00:29:12,105
Wasn't that your nickname?
Gravel? Pebble?

572
00:29:12,189 --> 00:29:13,607
Or something like that.

573
00:29:14,232 --> 00:29:15,525
What an absurd nickname.

574
00:29:15,609 --> 00:29:17,527
Instead of a measly pebble,

575
00:29:17,611 --> 00:29:18,904
I shall be a chunk of rock.

576
00:29:18,987 --> 00:29:20,051
If anyone messes with me,

577
00:29:20,151 --> 00:29:22,157
this chunk of rock
will come crashing down.

578
00:29:23,450 --> 00:29:26,203
Yeah. "Chunk of rock"
suits you better than "pebble."

579
00:29:31,792 --> 00:29:32,918
So salty!

580
00:29:33,001 --> 00:29:34,586
Did you think seawater would be sweet?

581
00:29:34,669 --> 00:29:35,754
Why would you taste that?

582
00:29:35,837 --> 00:29:36,797
I see.

583
00:29:37,506 --> 00:29:39,091
Seawater is quite salty.

584
00:29:47,140 --> 00:29:49,393
I am truly glad to be alive.

585
00:29:50,227 --> 00:29:51,895
The sea dyed by the sunset

586
00:29:53,021 --> 00:29:54,439
is ridiculously beautiful.

587
00:29:55,107 --> 00:29:57,484
You've been going on like some old lady.

588
00:29:57,567 --> 00:29:59,236
What, are you back from the dead?

589
00:30:01,530 --> 00:30:03,031
It is because I am happy.

590
00:30:04,991 --> 00:30:06,368
I am so happy to be alive.

591
00:30:43,405 --> 00:30:45,073
It's Yoon Ji-hyo.

592
00:30:47,617 --> 00:30:49,202
It's a private villa, right?

593
00:30:49,286 --> 00:30:51,496
I heard the security was airtight.

594
00:30:52,372 --> 00:30:53,498
She's pretty, right?

595
00:30:55,959 --> 00:30:57,919
I apologize.
Would you like a tour of the resort?

596
00:30:58,003 --> 00:30:59,671
Or to head straight to your room?

597
00:31:00,672 --> 00:31:01,673
To the room.

598
00:31:01,756 --> 00:31:03,175
Sure. Just give me a moment.

599
00:31:05,677 --> 00:31:07,637
Excuse me, but you can't film here.

600
00:31:07,721 --> 00:31:09,306
-Okay.
-Sorry about that.

601
00:31:12,267 --> 00:31:13,268
Shin Seo-ri?

602
00:31:14,102 --> 00:31:15,353
Cha and his aide?

603
00:31:15,437 --> 00:31:16,938
What a scandal.

604
00:31:17,981 --> 00:31:19,024
Wow.

605
00:31:19,733 --> 00:31:22,027
What do you want for dinner?
I can look for a place.

606
00:31:22,110 --> 00:31:24,946
Since we are by the sea,
let us eat ostrea.

607
00:31:25,030 --> 00:31:26,698
According to the <i>Dongui Bogam,</i>

608
00:31:26,781 --> 00:31:28,200
consuming it refines the skin

609
00:31:28,283 --> 00:31:30,076
and improves one's complexion.

610
00:31:30,160 --> 00:31:31,870
The finest tonic the sea has to offer.

611
00:31:31,953 --> 00:31:33,371
"Ostrea"? Is that a type of meat?

612
00:31:33,455 --> 00:31:35,081
You do not know what ostrea is?

613
00:31:35,165 --> 00:31:37,501
Its white, milky flesh tends
to be quite plump--

614
00:31:37,584 --> 00:31:38,793
Octopus?

615
00:31:39,461 --> 00:31:40,545
No, not that.

616
00:31:40,629 --> 00:31:42,130
It is sweet when grilled,

617
00:31:42,214 --> 00:31:44,382
and as a soup,
the broth is so refreshing.

618
00:31:44,466 --> 00:31:46,051
-Hairtail?
-No!

619
00:31:46,134 --> 00:31:49,304
You can eat the meat
and grind the leftover shells into powder

620
00:31:49,387 --> 00:31:51,097
that can be used to calm a racing heart

621
00:31:51,181 --> 00:31:53,058
and aid a man's nocturnal emissions.

622
00:31:53,141 --> 00:31:55,523
Both food and remedy,
not a single part wasted--

623
00:31:55,606 --> 00:31:57,687
Right. So what is it exactly?

624
00:31:57,771 --> 00:31:58,980
Could it be oysters?

625
00:31:59,064 --> 00:32:00,023
Oysters?

626
00:32:00,106 --> 00:32:01,900
My grandpa used to run an apothecary.

627
00:32:01,983 --> 00:32:03,860
Apothecaries call oysters "ostrea."

628
00:32:03,944 --> 00:32:06,404
Yes, that's it! Oysters. Ostrea.

629
00:32:06,488 --> 00:32:08,865
Just say it normally.
Did we really need to play 20 Questions?

630
00:32:08,949 --> 00:32:10,867
Do you really expect me
to solve all your riddles?

631
00:32:10,951 --> 00:32:12,244
Even if I speak like a fool,

632
00:32:12,327 --> 00:32:14,621
my servant should understand
like a genius.

633
00:32:14,704 --> 00:32:16,414
I can't eat oysters. Bad stomach.

634
00:32:16,498 --> 00:32:18,875
Nobody asked for the servant's opinion.

635
00:32:19,793 --> 00:32:21,086
Who's that?

636
00:32:28,176 --> 00:32:30,512
Shin Seo-ri, that loser, has a boyfriend?

637
00:32:32,055 --> 00:32:34,391
Is that guy Mr. Supercar?

638
00:32:34,474 --> 00:32:36,268
-How about black pork?
-Sounds good.

639
00:32:36,351 --> 00:32:38,812
We are by the sea, so we must eat ostrea.

640
00:32:38,895 --> 00:32:41,898
But he looks way too shabby to own one.

641
00:32:43,775 --> 00:32:46,361
Jeez. Who knew a trip to Tamna
would be so damn exhausting?

642
00:32:46,444 --> 00:32:48,446
Wow, it's so spacious.

643
00:32:48,530 --> 00:32:49,573
The TV is huge too.

644
00:32:49,656 --> 00:32:51,157
-You're late.
-Goodness me.

645
00:32:51,241 --> 00:32:52,242
What took you so long?

646
00:32:52,325 --> 00:32:54,786
Why are you so surprised?
Guilty conscience?

647
00:32:56,413 --> 00:32:59,165
Oh, you must be Seo-ri's manager.

648
00:32:59,249 --> 00:33:00,834
Gwang-nam, right?

649
00:33:00,917 --> 00:33:01,793
Right?

650
00:33:02,544 --> 00:33:03,587
Nice to meet you.

651
00:33:04,254 --> 00:33:06,172
Let's do some good work together.

652
00:33:07,299 --> 00:33:09,467
Oh right. The ad agency said

653
00:33:09,551 --> 00:33:11,094
Mr. Cha's team is staying here as well.

654
00:33:11,177 --> 00:33:12,846
Tell them I'll treat them to dinner.

655
00:33:12,929 --> 00:33:14,306
Yes, ma'am.

656
00:33:20,228 --> 00:33:22,689
Calling to invite them is bad manners.

657
00:33:22,772 --> 00:33:24,441
You must go and tell them in person.

658
00:33:24,524 --> 00:33:26,943
Making me run around like a dog.

659
00:33:30,822 --> 00:33:33,700
Seo-ri, where in the world
did you find a kid like him?

660
00:33:33,783 --> 00:33:35,827
Why are you here unannounced, Ms. Hong?

661
00:33:37,120 --> 00:33:38,997
Where the needle goes, the thread follows.

662
00:33:39,080 --> 00:33:41,166
Why wouldn't I be here for your shoot?

663
00:33:41,875 --> 00:33:44,628
I thought that minx
was your needle, not me.

664
00:33:44,711 --> 00:33:46,796
Ji-hyo is completely drained right now.

665
00:33:46,880 --> 00:33:48,465
She went far away to recharge.

666
00:33:49,090 --> 00:33:49,966
Far away?

667
00:33:50,508 --> 00:33:51,384
Where?

668
00:33:59,184 --> 00:34:01,519
Damn it. There are couples everywhere.

669
00:34:01,603 --> 00:34:03,188
Maybe I should've gone camping?

670
00:34:04,522 --> 00:34:06,274
-Wait.
-He says he just wants to rest.

671
00:34:06,358 --> 00:34:08,318
Okay, I'll pass that on.

672
00:34:09,152 --> 00:34:10,612
Hold on. You have some dust.

673
00:34:11,946 --> 00:34:13,531
-You're good now.
-Thank you.

674
00:34:14,240 --> 00:34:16,117
You have some on your back too.

675
00:34:16,201 --> 00:34:18,495
-Maybe he really is Mr. Supercar?
-Thanks.

676
00:34:22,165 --> 00:34:23,708
Wait, he's coming here.

677
00:34:23,792 --> 00:34:25,251
He's coming right towards me.

678
00:34:37,681 --> 00:34:38,598
What the…

679
00:34:51,319 --> 00:34:53,697
Hello, my name is Baek Gwang-nam.

680
00:34:53,780 --> 00:34:54,864
Excuse me?

681
00:34:54,948 --> 00:34:57,867
Well, it looked like you were on vacation,

682
00:34:57,951 --> 00:34:59,619
so I didn't want to bother you,

683
00:34:59,703 --> 00:35:02,414
but I gathered up the courage
and decided to say hi.

684
00:35:02,497 --> 00:35:04,124
Oh, I see.

685
00:35:04,207 --> 00:35:05,667
I'm a huge fan.

686
00:35:07,168 --> 00:35:10,296
I saw on Insta that you were on vacation,

687
00:35:10,380 --> 00:35:13,007
but I never expected
to run into you like this.

688
00:35:13,550 --> 00:35:14,634
You're a fan of mine?

689
00:35:14,718 --> 00:35:16,010
Yes, a huge fan.

690
00:35:17,137 --> 00:35:18,596
You're really heavenly in person.

691
00:35:19,556 --> 00:35:21,182
An angel on screen too.

692
00:35:22,684 --> 00:35:23,727
Right.

693
00:35:25,854 --> 00:35:27,355
I can't believe this.

694
00:35:27,981 --> 00:35:30,275
Well, do you want to take a selfie?

695
00:35:30,358 --> 00:35:33,027
I'm too nervous for that.
I don't think I could.

696
00:35:33,111 --> 00:35:34,571
Okay.

697
00:35:47,542 --> 00:35:49,210
At least he has a good eye.

698
00:35:50,295 --> 00:35:52,338
Hello, my name is Baek Gwang-nam.

699
00:35:55,049 --> 00:35:56,885
But…

700
00:35:56,968 --> 00:35:58,970
what's with the getup?

701
00:35:59,053 --> 00:36:00,597
Looking so raggedy.

702
00:36:01,222 --> 00:36:02,682
Or maybe it's vintage?

703
00:36:05,685 --> 00:36:07,896
They make a pretty good kimchi broth.

704
00:36:07,979 --> 00:36:09,439
We should've grilled some black pork.

705
00:36:09,522 --> 00:36:11,441
Why are we eating kimchi noodles?

706
00:36:11,524 --> 00:36:13,526
Let me know if you need anything else.

707
00:36:13,610 --> 00:36:14,903
I'll be right on it.

708
00:36:14,986 --> 00:36:16,112
That's enough.

709
00:36:16,196 --> 00:36:18,406
Just toast and be gone. I'm tired.

710
00:36:18,490 --> 00:36:20,700
-Okay. Cheers.
-Cheers.

711
00:36:22,994 --> 00:36:23,995
From now on,

712
00:36:24,078 --> 00:36:26,414
I intend to give this job
everything I have.

713
00:36:26,498 --> 00:36:27,707
Just leave it all to me.

714
00:36:29,167 --> 00:36:30,210
That's nice.

715
00:36:30,293 --> 00:36:32,253
We got this, Jeju Shoot Team!

716
00:36:33,129 --> 00:36:34,881
Have a good night!

717
00:36:39,344 --> 00:36:42,931
What's gotten into him?
He just suddenly decided to stop sulking?

718
00:36:43,014 --> 00:36:45,225
The human mind will forever elude us.

719
00:36:45,308 --> 00:36:46,267
I could not care less.

720
00:36:47,852 --> 00:36:50,146
Anyway, to finish what I was saying.

721
00:36:50,230 --> 00:36:53,233
The concept for this shoot is
"Jeju Goddess."

722
00:36:53,316 --> 00:36:54,317
No.

723
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:56,069
Is she possessed by the spirit of nudity?

724
00:36:56,152 --> 00:36:58,530
I mean, is she dressed or naked?

725
00:36:58,613 --> 00:36:59,906
That is profoundly vulgar.

726
00:36:59,989 --> 00:37:02,200
That's exactly the point.

727
00:37:02,283 --> 00:37:03,701
Look. Barely there.

728
00:37:03,785 --> 00:37:05,453
Almost see-through. You know?

729
00:37:05,537 --> 00:37:07,497
Look at Greek mythology.

730
00:37:08,081 --> 00:37:10,667
They're all butt-naked
and staring right at you.

731
00:37:10,750 --> 00:37:12,252
Gods have no shame.

732
00:37:12,335 --> 00:37:14,254
That's just how they are.

733
00:37:15,004 --> 00:37:16,714
-Really?
-Yeah.

734
00:37:18,174 --> 00:37:21,052
Our bodies will just rot away
when we die anyway.

735
00:37:21,678 --> 00:37:25,098
We must use our beauty at its peak
to make it worthwhile.

736
00:37:25,181 --> 00:37:26,182
Exactly.

737
00:37:26,808 --> 00:37:28,393
All right. If I am doing this,

738
00:37:28,476 --> 00:37:31,020
I might as well
go all out and show it all off.

739
00:37:31,104 --> 00:37:32,188
That's the spirit.

740
00:37:32,272 --> 00:37:33,273
Cheers.

741
00:37:49,038 --> 00:37:50,456
You look a bit pale, sir.

742
00:37:51,124 --> 00:37:53,376
Yeah. I just didn't sleep well last night.

743
00:37:53,459 --> 00:37:56,296
You should be resting at the hotel.
Why are you out here?

744
00:37:57,755 --> 00:37:59,799
Never mind that. Where's the model?

745
00:38:00,758 --> 00:38:01,634
There…

746
00:38:03,303 --> 00:38:04,971
she is. Ms. Shin Seo-ri.

747
00:38:31,664 --> 00:38:33,041
Hello.

748
00:38:33,124 --> 00:38:35,835
-Hello.
-Hello there.

749
00:38:36,628 --> 00:38:39,589
They weren't kidding.
The clothes really do make the person.

750
00:38:42,550 --> 00:38:44,469
What do you think, Mr. Cha?

751
00:38:56,481 --> 00:38:58,733
Don't you think
that outfit is a bit too much?

752
00:38:58,816 --> 00:39:00,693
You must be kidding, Mr. Cha.

753
00:39:00,777 --> 00:39:02,654
She looks absolutely gorgeous.

754
00:39:02,737 --> 00:39:05,239
Seo-ri, maybe we can try
moving around a bit. Yeah.

755
00:39:12,664 --> 00:39:14,207
Change her outfit. Right now.

756
00:39:14,832 --> 00:39:17,043
-Please go change.
-Let's go change.

757
00:39:27,387 --> 00:39:30,098
The design is too haute couture. Next.

758
00:39:31,307 --> 00:39:32,767
We'll be right back.

759
00:39:40,692 --> 00:39:42,902
And this one is too prêt-à-porter.

760
00:39:42,986 --> 00:39:44,112
Swap.

761
00:39:52,912 --> 00:39:55,790
I mean,
what's up with all these clothes?

762
00:39:56,708 --> 00:39:58,751
I don't even know where to look.

763
00:39:58,835 --> 00:40:00,545
Am I some mutt you are trying to train?

764
00:40:00,628 --> 00:40:01,963
-Your eyes are the issue.
-Come on.

765
00:40:02,046 --> 00:40:03,673
Are your eyes possessed or something?

766
00:40:03,756 --> 00:40:05,883
-Stop it.
-Let go of me! Why, that little…

767
00:40:07,385 --> 00:40:08,261
Hold on.

768
00:40:08,803 --> 00:40:10,513
-Manager Baek!
-No, let's not do that.

769
00:40:11,597 --> 00:40:13,516
Come on, Mr. Cha.

770
00:40:14,183 --> 00:40:17,103
The marketing team signed off
on the final concept,

771
00:40:17,186 --> 00:40:20,648
and you personally approved these outfits.

772
00:40:20,732 --> 00:40:22,650
You can't just change them suddenly.

773
00:40:22,734 --> 00:40:25,236
The photos didn't show the fabric quality.

774
00:40:25,319 --> 00:40:27,321
This is an ad campaign,
not a personal photo shoot.

775
00:40:27,405 --> 00:40:29,657
The model stands out
way too much right now.

776
00:40:31,743 --> 00:40:33,411
She doesn't stand out <i>that</i> much.

777
00:40:33,494 --> 00:40:35,121
Her very being stands out too much.

778
00:40:35,204 --> 00:40:37,206
The outfit suits the location well.

779
00:40:37,290 --> 00:40:38,583
Screw the location.

780
00:40:38,666 --> 00:40:40,835
She's the only thing I can see right now!

781
00:40:43,212 --> 00:40:45,465
It looks fine. What's wrong with him?

782
00:40:45,548 --> 00:40:47,008
Why can't he just approve it?

783
00:40:51,971 --> 00:40:54,891
Replace all the outfits
and get my approval again.

784
00:40:54,974 --> 00:40:57,435
I'm the advertiser,
so you should meet my needs.

785
00:40:57,518 --> 00:40:58,644
Yes, sir.

786
00:41:01,689 --> 00:41:03,232
Why are my legs so numb?

787
00:41:09,906 --> 00:41:12,366
<i>The person you are trying</i>
<i>to reach is unavailable…</i>

788
00:41:15,411 --> 00:41:17,121
Ms. An Seong-hui, are you home?

789
00:41:19,582 --> 00:41:20,750
Ms. An Seong-hui?

790
00:41:21,375 --> 00:41:23,377
I'm from Biojei.

791
00:41:25,004 --> 00:41:26,714
Ms. An Seong-hui, are you home?

792
00:41:28,925 --> 00:41:30,093
Ms. An Seong-hui?

793
00:41:33,179 --> 00:41:35,223
We handled the nurse as instructed.

794
00:41:35,306 --> 00:41:36,682
How did Cha Se-gye react?

795
00:41:36,766 --> 00:41:39,018
Without proof, it seems he decided

796
00:41:39,102 --> 00:41:40,478
to stick to his schedule.

797
00:41:40,561 --> 00:41:41,994
Word from the set is a bit strange.

798
00:41:42,063 --> 00:41:44,816
He began interfering heavily
before shooting even began,

799
00:41:44,899 --> 00:41:46,526
causing some friction.

800
00:41:46,609 --> 00:41:49,195
He kept changing the model's outfits,

801
00:41:49,278 --> 00:41:50,905
upsetting the crew.

802
00:41:51,489 --> 00:41:52,698
Changing outfits?

803
00:41:55,660 --> 00:41:56,536
How amusing.

804
00:42:00,289 --> 00:42:01,249
It seems

805
00:42:02,834 --> 00:42:04,710
the time has come.

806
00:42:09,006 --> 00:42:11,843
Excuse me,
can I ask you for a little help?

807
00:42:11,926 --> 00:42:14,011
My grandson got lost.

808
00:42:14,095 --> 00:42:15,012
Your grandson?

809
00:42:17,140 --> 00:42:19,934
I am not so meddlesome that I would go
searching for some stranger's kid.

810
00:42:20,017 --> 00:42:21,853
I'll make it worth your while.

811
00:42:21,936 --> 00:42:24,438
Here. This is licorice taffy.

812
00:42:24,522 --> 00:42:26,357
Boiled with honey for three days.

813
00:42:26,440 --> 00:42:27,900
I'll give you this too.

814
00:42:28,609 --> 00:42:29,986
NODO MANAGER BAEK GWANG-NAM

815
00:42:40,121 --> 00:42:42,081
WE DISCOVERED THE QUEEN OF DYNAESTIE
GREAT JOB, EVERYONE!

816
00:42:43,291 --> 00:42:44,625
Is Seo-ri still not answering?

817
00:42:44,709 --> 00:42:46,961
I called over ten times
and checked her room.

818
00:42:47,044 --> 00:42:47,962
I can't find her.

819
00:42:48,045 --> 00:42:50,882
Then you should send people out
to find her. What are you doing?

820
00:42:50,965 --> 00:42:52,258
Don't worry.

821
00:42:52,341 --> 00:42:54,302
Maybe she went to get a snack--

822
00:42:54,385 --> 00:42:57,597
Where's she going this late
when she doesn't even know her way around?

823
00:42:59,015 --> 00:43:00,433
You should stay here, sir.

824
00:43:00,516 --> 00:43:02,685
It'll only make her look bad
if you leave now.

825
00:43:02,768 --> 00:43:04,562
The crew is already upset over the delays

826
00:43:04,645 --> 00:43:06,814
caused by all the wardrobe changes.

827
00:43:06,898 --> 00:43:08,566
It'll only start weird rumors.

828
00:43:11,903 --> 00:43:13,112
What do I…

829
00:43:14,363 --> 00:43:16,240
All right. Thanks.

830
00:43:18,326 --> 00:43:19,619
Sir, can we step outside?

831
00:43:21,287 --> 00:43:24,749
Ms. Kim found her and is taking her
to a nearby hospital.

832
00:43:24,832 --> 00:43:26,042
And the nurse's current state?

833
00:43:26,125 --> 00:43:27,543
They say she's stable,

834
00:43:27,627 --> 00:43:30,379
but she hasn't woken up yet,
so we have to wait.

835
00:43:41,599 --> 00:43:43,392
Sir, where are you…

836
00:43:43,976 --> 00:43:47,730
Our policy prohibits sharing this footage
with the guests.

837
00:43:47,813 --> 00:43:50,358
But since you said it's an emergency…

838
00:43:51,150 --> 00:43:52,276
-Stop there.
-What?

839
00:43:52,360 --> 00:43:54,278
-Bottom right, third one.
-Here?

840
00:44:11,045 --> 00:44:14,423
I mean, this is like
finding a needle in a haystack.

841
00:44:15,091 --> 00:44:16,968
We should let your family know

842
00:44:17,843 --> 00:44:19,971
or get more men to help out.

843
00:44:20,054 --> 00:44:22,640
If it is just us,
we will end up going in circles all night.

844
00:44:22,723 --> 00:44:24,475
Gosh, I am sorry.

845
00:44:24,558 --> 00:44:26,269
We shouldn't have rushed here.

846
00:44:26,894 --> 00:44:30,147
You're going through
all this trouble because of me.

847
00:44:30,898 --> 00:44:32,024
My goodness.

848
00:44:32,566 --> 00:44:33,484
Wait.

849
00:44:34,151 --> 00:44:36,612
-Jeez. What happened?
-Oh no.

850
00:44:38,447 --> 00:44:39,865
Don't worry.

851
00:44:39,949 --> 00:44:41,784
I'll make you a fresh batch.

852
00:44:43,244 --> 00:44:45,288
Never mind that. Think carefully.

853
00:44:45,371 --> 00:44:46,914
Whereabouts did he let go of your hand?

854
00:44:46,998 --> 00:44:47,999
I'm sure

855
00:44:48,624 --> 00:44:50,001
it was around here

856
00:44:50,668 --> 00:44:52,378
that he disappeared.

857
00:44:53,337 --> 00:44:54,213
Goodness.

858
00:44:54,297 --> 00:44:55,923
How old is your grandson?

859
00:44:56,007 --> 00:44:57,925
He's 6 years old.

860
00:44:58,009 --> 00:45:00,386
My Hyeon-ho is 6.

861
00:45:00,469 --> 00:45:02,346
You look to be at least 80,

862
00:45:02,430 --> 00:45:04,265
but your grandson is only 6?

863
00:45:05,433 --> 00:45:07,310
How old are you, old man?

864
00:45:07,393 --> 00:45:09,020
Old man? What do you mean?

865
00:45:09,103 --> 00:45:10,938
I just got married early.

866
00:45:11,022 --> 00:45:13,399
I'm only 55 years old.

867
00:45:15,693 --> 00:45:16,777
Fifty-five?

868
00:45:22,450 --> 00:45:23,576
Grandpa!

869
00:45:24,493 --> 00:45:25,661
What are you doing?

870
00:45:32,209 --> 00:45:33,377
Mom and Dad

871
00:45:33,461 --> 00:45:35,254
went to the police to find you.

872
00:45:35,338 --> 00:45:36,589
Where have you been?

873
00:45:37,965 --> 00:45:39,133
Who are you?

874
00:45:41,302 --> 00:45:43,220
Gosh, I'm so sorry.

875
00:45:43,304 --> 00:45:44,472
My grandfather came to see me…

876
00:45:44,555 --> 00:45:45,431
SONG HYEON-HO

877
00:45:45,514 --> 00:45:46,891
…and must have gotten lost.

878
00:45:48,434 --> 00:45:50,770
Your party was looking for you.

879
00:45:52,271 --> 00:45:54,899
Grandpa! Where are you going now?

880
00:45:58,669 --> 00:45:59,545
Could it be dotage?

881
00:45:59,629 --> 00:46:00,504
DOTAGE: DEMENTIA

882
00:46:00,571 --> 00:46:01,864
SEORI'S NOODLE SHOP

883
00:46:01,947 --> 00:46:03,074
My goodness.

884
00:46:08,746 --> 00:46:10,623
Her after school class
should've ended by now.

885
00:46:10,706 --> 00:46:12,666
What's taking her so long?

886
00:46:13,417 --> 00:46:15,169
She must be hungry.

887
00:47:10,933 --> 00:47:12,268
Hello, sir.

888
00:47:12,351 --> 00:47:13,519
I'm a bit busy right now.

889
00:47:13,602 --> 00:47:15,563
Did your guest make it back okay?

890
00:47:15,646 --> 00:47:17,231
You saw her? Where?

891
00:47:17,940 --> 00:47:20,359
We would've been in serious trouble
without her help.

892
00:47:20,443 --> 00:47:21,986
My grandfather got lost--

893
00:47:22,069 --> 00:47:24,196
Where is she right now?

894
00:47:24,989 --> 00:47:25,990
I saw her earlier

895
00:47:26,073 --> 00:47:27,992
in the woods near the beach,
but I'm not sure…

896
00:47:28,075 --> 00:47:29,076
Damn it.

897
00:47:58,105 --> 00:47:59,857
<i>Why she brought in someone like you…</i>

898
00:48:12,286 --> 00:48:14,163
<i>Is anyone out there?</i>

899
00:48:14,246 --> 00:48:15,456
<i>Please help me!</i>

900
00:49:20,563 --> 00:49:22,731
Are you okay? Are you hurt anywhere?

901
00:49:31,198 --> 00:49:33,534
Why are you suddenly trying to be a hero?

902
00:49:33,617 --> 00:49:35,869
You don't know the area.
How could you have found anyone?

903
00:49:35,953 --> 00:49:38,414
I was not trying to be a hero.

904
00:49:39,331 --> 00:49:41,041
The old man kept clinging to me.

905
00:49:41,125 --> 00:49:44,503
You're not the type to just accept
anyone who latches on. Why help?

906
00:49:44,587 --> 00:49:46,463
Why are you suddenly such a busybody?

907
00:49:50,509 --> 00:49:52,303
Why do you care if I am being

908
00:49:53,512 --> 00:49:54,680
a busybody or not?

909
00:49:54,763 --> 00:49:55,723
Of course I care.

910
00:49:55,806 --> 00:49:58,767
We're on a business trip.
You can't just go off on your own.

911
00:49:58,851 --> 00:50:00,102
Do not be angry.

912
00:50:01,103 --> 00:50:02,354
What did I do so wrong--

913
00:50:02,438 --> 00:50:03,814
You were wrong

914
00:50:03,897 --> 00:50:06,483
to blindly follow a stranger at night.

915
00:50:06,567 --> 00:50:08,485
What if something happened to you?

916
00:50:13,198 --> 00:50:16,368
Are you this angry
because you were worried about me?

917
00:50:16,452 --> 00:50:18,037
Because I could have been hurt?

918
00:50:18,829 --> 00:50:21,123
Don't twist my words.
Keep work and private life separate.

919
00:50:21,206 --> 00:50:23,959
You were late for work
because of your personal actions.

920
00:50:24,043 --> 00:50:26,128
A nuisance to your colleagues.
Am I wrong?

921
00:50:26,920 --> 00:50:27,838
A nuisance?

922
00:50:28,339 --> 00:50:30,674
Yes. Poking around everywhere

923
00:50:30,758 --> 00:50:32,718
and meddling all day.

924
00:50:32,801 --> 00:50:35,471
Professionally, it's an obstruction.
Privately, it's a waste of time.

925
00:50:35,554 --> 00:50:37,598
So please! God damn it.

926
00:50:38,599 --> 00:50:40,851
Just stay out of trouble, please.

927
00:50:47,691 --> 00:50:49,276
Very well, I understand.

928
00:50:49,360 --> 00:50:51,028
I shall take care not to be a nuisance.

929
00:50:51,111 --> 00:50:53,947
So do not come looking for me
like this next time.

930
00:50:54,031 --> 00:50:56,867
I too shall treat you
as a complete stranger from now on.

931
00:51:10,756 --> 00:51:11,882
Great work, everyone.

932
00:51:29,441 --> 00:51:31,694
-May I have your attention, please?
-Yes.

933
00:51:31,777 --> 00:51:34,113
Please let me apologize.
My grandfather lost his way,

934
00:51:34,196 --> 00:51:36,031
but Ms. Shin Seo-ri helped me find him.

935
00:51:36,115 --> 00:51:37,700
That was what made her late.

936
00:51:40,703 --> 00:51:42,121
Is that true?

937
00:51:42,204 --> 00:51:44,248
Well, I did not exactly help find him.

938
00:51:44,331 --> 00:51:47,084
Do you break out in hives
when you do good deeds?

939
00:51:47,167 --> 00:51:49,211
His grandson confirmed it.
Why keep denying it?

940
00:51:49,294 --> 00:51:51,463
Please allow me to offer
a bottle of Premier Cru Burgundy

941
00:51:51,547 --> 00:51:53,632
for each table.

942
00:51:55,467 --> 00:51:56,719
-Wow.
-Wow.

943
00:51:58,971 --> 00:52:02,099
-Shin Seo-ri!
-Shin Seo-ri!

944
00:52:02,182 --> 00:52:04,935
-Shin Seo-ri!
-Shin Seo-ri!

945
00:52:05,018 --> 00:52:07,062
-Thank you for the wine!
-Shin Seo-ri!

946
00:52:08,772 --> 00:52:10,941
Thank you for the wine!

947
00:52:20,492 --> 00:52:22,369
Now, have you ever heard of it?

948
00:52:22,453 --> 00:52:24,788
This has gone unrecorded for 500 years.

949
00:52:24,872 --> 00:52:26,582
It is the Chaos Wine of Joseon.

950
00:52:26,665 --> 00:52:29,960
<i>Makgeolli</i> mixed with wine.
The perfect harmony of East and West.

951
00:52:30,502 --> 00:52:32,421
And I am the only one who can brew it.

952
00:52:35,466 --> 00:52:36,550
Drink up!

953
00:52:36,633 --> 00:52:38,302
-Drink up!
-Drink up!

954
00:52:51,148 --> 00:52:52,858
I'm not drinking tonight.

955
00:52:52,941 --> 00:52:54,193
Come on.

956
00:52:54,276 --> 00:52:56,820
Drink, Mr. Son! Drink!

957
00:52:56,904 --> 00:52:58,739
-Drink!
-Drink!

958
00:52:58,822 --> 00:53:01,992
-Down the hatch! Chug!
-Down the hatch! Chug!

959
00:53:02,075 --> 00:53:03,660
-Chug!
-Chug!

960
00:53:03,744 --> 00:53:06,368
-How long will you make us dance?
-How long will you make us dance?

961
00:53:06,455 --> 00:53:07,331
Mr. Son.

962
00:53:07,414 --> 00:53:09,666
-Look at my dislocated shoulders!
-Look at my dislocated shoulders!

963
00:53:09,750 --> 00:53:10,626
Mr. Son!

964
00:53:10,709 --> 00:53:12,461
-Wow!
-Wow!

965
00:53:14,588 --> 00:53:15,881
Wait!

966
00:53:15,964 --> 00:53:18,008
Michelin class? No?

967
00:53:22,930 --> 00:53:24,890
I'll have one more. This is so good.

968
00:53:24,973 --> 00:53:26,683
-Mr. Son.
-Yes, Michelin.

969
00:53:26,767 --> 00:53:29,061
Isn't this after-party
an extension of work?

970
00:53:29,144 --> 00:53:30,604
Pace yourself.

971
00:53:32,147 --> 00:53:33,732
No fun!

972
00:53:34,358 --> 00:53:35,400
What are you even doing?

973
00:53:35,484 --> 00:53:37,236
Not drinking at a drinking party,

974
00:53:37,319 --> 00:53:39,905
just sitting around chattering
like a petty little miser.

975
00:53:40,948 --> 00:53:43,116
You should have a glass too, Lord CEO.

976
00:53:44,076 --> 00:53:47,955
-Drink!
-Drink!

977
00:53:48,038 --> 00:53:51,625
-Drink!
-Drink!

978
00:53:51,708 --> 00:53:53,418
I'm not drinking.

979
00:53:54,044 --> 00:53:55,295
Come on, drink.

980
00:53:56,171 --> 00:53:58,799
Being the only sober one
among drunks is no fun.

981
00:53:58,882 --> 00:54:00,926
I'm more comfortable
being sober and boring.

982
00:54:01,760 --> 00:54:04,304
It is not about comfort.
You just cannot drink.

983
00:54:04,388 --> 00:54:05,931
The petty little miser cannot handle

984
00:54:06,014 --> 00:54:07,641
a glass of Chaos Wine and chatters away.

985
00:54:07,724 --> 00:54:10,185
I told you it's not that I can't.
I just don't want to.

986
00:54:10,269 --> 00:54:12,062
Didn't you say you'd treat me
like a stranger?

987
00:54:12,145 --> 00:54:15,399
We may be strangers in private,
but not professionally.

988
00:54:15,482 --> 00:54:17,276
The lightweight who talks a big game.

989
00:54:17,359 --> 00:54:18,527
I am <i>choosing</i> not to drink.

990
00:54:18,610 --> 00:54:20,320
If you are that scared, let me.

991
00:54:20,404 --> 00:54:22,030
Hand it over.

992
00:54:22,114 --> 00:54:23,323
Who says I'm scared?

993
00:54:32,082 --> 00:54:34,501
-What a man!
-One more!

994
00:54:34,585 --> 00:54:37,504
You can drink just fine,
yet you put up such a fuss.

995
00:54:37,588 --> 00:54:39,965
You should have just tossed it back
like that from the start.

996
00:54:40,048 --> 00:54:43,719
Lord CEO,
you sure love playing hard to get.

997
00:54:55,063 --> 00:54:57,441
<i>Right, why take things so seriously?</i>

998
00:54:57,524 --> 00:55:00,068
<i>I get to be this drunk because I am alive.</i>

999
00:55:00,152 --> 00:55:03,071
<i>Worldly anguish,</i>
<i>pointless worries and the like</i>

1000
00:55:03,155 --> 00:55:05,866
<i>can all be washed away</i>
<i>with a single drink.</i>

1001
00:55:12,748 --> 00:55:14,583
<i>Once a gloomy day passes,</i>

1002
00:55:14,666 --> 00:55:16,919
<i>a pleasant new sun is bound to rise.</i>

1003
00:55:17,002 --> 00:55:19,838
Gosh, why is it so cold?

1004
00:55:27,012 --> 00:55:29,097
Dawn is still a long way away.

1005
00:55:31,683 --> 00:55:33,268
And where am I now?

1006
00:55:37,105 --> 00:55:39,524
Where did everyone run off to without me?

1007
00:55:39,608 --> 00:55:41,985
And you wonder
why I can't take my eyes off you?

1008
00:55:44,780 --> 00:55:46,490
A stranger is speaking to me.

1009
00:55:47,407 --> 00:55:49,534
Do you know me? I do not recognize you.

1010
00:55:50,911 --> 00:55:52,412
You're drunk, Shin Seo-ri.

1011
00:55:55,707 --> 00:55:56,708
Drunk, my foot.

1012
00:55:57,459 --> 00:55:58,794
I am perfectly sober.

1013
00:55:58,877 --> 00:56:00,796
Here, look how perfectly sober I am.

1014
00:56:03,006 --> 00:56:04,341
I told you to watch it!

1015
00:56:05,217 --> 00:56:06,802
Watch that degenerate behavior!

1016
00:56:24,319 --> 00:56:25,821
"The moon rises, luminous."

1017
00:56:26,405 --> 00:56:27,656
"The beauty, how lovely."

1018
00:56:28,407 --> 00:56:30,158
"Gracefully entwining, unfolding."

1019
00:56:30,242 --> 00:56:31,743
"My troubled heart…"

1020
00:56:33,537 --> 00:56:36,873
"The bright moon rises,
revealing my beautiful love."

1021
00:56:37,416 --> 00:56:39,376
"My heart aches in longing."

1022
00:56:42,462 --> 00:56:43,880
Cha Se-gye.

1023
00:56:44,464 --> 00:56:46,133
I must go to Mount Halla,

1024
00:56:46,883 --> 00:56:49,011
-so lead the way.
-Why Mount Halla?

1025
00:56:49,094 --> 00:56:51,638
I have something to say there.

1026
00:56:52,764 --> 00:56:54,016
I must declare

1027
00:56:54,099 --> 00:56:56,977
that I shall cast myself away
and live as Shin Seo-ri.

1028
00:56:57,519 --> 00:57:00,647
Must you make that declaration
at Mount Halla, at this hour?

1029
00:57:00,731 --> 00:57:01,690
Silence!

1030
00:57:02,274 --> 00:57:03,692
Do you truly not know?

1031
00:57:03,775 --> 00:57:05,819
<i>My Lovely Sam Soon,</i> Episode 12.

1032
00:57:06,445 --> 00:57:08,989
Sam-soon cleanses herself
of her tedious past

1033
00:57:09,072 --> 00:57:11,742
and declares her new life
as Kim Hee-jin.

1034
00:57:11,825 --> 00:57:14,077
That very scene struck
a chord in my heart.

1035
00:57:15,829 --> 00:57:17,789
With Mount Halla so close at hand,

1036
00:57:17,873 --> 00:57:20,333
I cannot miss such a golden opportunity.

1037
00:57:21,043 --> 00:57:22,753
What are you talking about?

1038
00:57:22,836 --> 00:57:24,254
Shush. Let us go to Mount Halla!

1039
00:57:24,337 --> 00:57:25,547
I'm not going to Mount Halla.

1040
00:57:27,007 --> 00:57:28,925
Are you asking for palanquin fare?

1041
00:57:30,969 --> 00:57:32,304
Here.

1042
00:57:37,851 --> 00:57:39,728
When did you pick this up?

1043
00:57:47,486 --> 00:57:49,988
No! Stop! My token!

1044
00:57:50,072 --> 00:57:52,240
Are you nuts? Where are you going?

1045
00:57:52,324 --> 00:57:54,659
Why did you throw away my precious token?

1046
00:57:54,743 --> 00:57:55,952
I intended to cherish it.

1047
00:57:56,036 --> 00:57:57,329
You just said it was my fare.

1048
00:57:57,412 --> 00:57:59,289
Are you drunk?
Why would I pay with a rock?

1049
00:57:59,372 --> 00:58:00,540
It must be you who is drunk.

1050
00:58:00,624 --> 00:58:03,288
I stopped you going to Mount Halla,
even when you were freaking out.

1051
00:58:03,388 --> 00:58:05,563
Are you mad?
Climbing a mountain in the dead of night?

1052
00:58:05,638 --> 00:58:08,381
That's what I'm saying!
The sea is better than a mountain.

1053
00:58:12,803 --> 00:58:14,221
You said you liked the sea.

1054
00:58:15,931 --> 00:58:17,599
Just sober up a bit before we go.

1055
00:58:19,643 --> 00:58:21,019
Very well, then.

1056
00:58:26,024 --> 00:58:27,109
Cha Se-gye!

1057
00:58:29,986 --> 00:58:31,321
Look at that.

1058
00:59:04,563 --> 00:59:05,564
Hello.

1059
00:59:08,483 --> 00:59:09,484
Ms. Mo Tae-hee.

1060
00:59:16,908 --> 00:59:19,035
The sea has parted in two.

1061
00:59:19,119 --> 00:59:21,204
Maybe I drank too much Chaos Wine?

1062
00:59:21,288 --> 00:59:23,290
I told you yesterday. It's low tide.

1063
00:59:23,373 --> 00:59:26,251
It becomes a path at ebb tide
and an island at high tide.

1064
00:59:26,334 --> 00:59:27,836
It must be nice to be so smart,

1065
00:59:27,919 --> 00:59:29,212
knowing everything in the world.

1066
00:59:29,296 --> 00:59:31,715
Don't you think there's just too much
you don't know?

1067
00:59:31,798 --> 00:59:34,301
Yet there is one thing I know for certain.

1068
00:59:35,177 --> 00:59:36,761
How to endure life.

1069
00:59:37,929 --> 00:59:41,183
To ensure good memories
are not easily forgotten,

1070
00:59:42,225 --> 00:59:44,477
one must collect tokens like this.

1071
00:59:46,229 --> 00:59:48,398
I have tucked away the fond memory

1072
00:59:48,982 --> 00:59:50,525
of seeing the sea for the first time.

1073
00:59:50,609 --> 00:59:52,611
When life becomes unbearable,

1074
00:59:53,153 --> 00:59:54,696
I shall reach deep down

1075
00:59:55,405 --> 00:59:57,824
and pull out the memories
of those good times.

1076
00:59:58,992 --> 01:00:00,952
What if the good memories make you sad?

1077
01:00:03,872 --> 01:00:05,040
What then?

1078
01:00:06,625 --> 01:00:08,418
A memory both good and sad?

1079
01:00:10,086 --> 01:00:11,546
You must tuck it back away.

1080
01:00:12,088 --> 01:00:14,549
Since recalling it
will only make you weak,

1081
01:00:15,091 --> 01:00:16,843
you must replace it with new ones.

1082
01:00:22,140 --> 01:00:23,225
You…

1083
01:00:25,185 --> 01:00:26,603
feel guilty, do you not?

1084
01:00:29,147 --> 01:00:30,148
What?

1085
01:00:31,775 --> 01:00:33,443
It is written all over your face.

1086
01:00:34,778 --> 01:00:36,238
That you feel sorry.

1087
01:00:36,321 --> 01:00:38,448
That you regret losing
your temper earlier.

1088
01:00:41,368 --> 01:00:42,702
But it is quite all right.

1089
01:00:43,328 --> 01:00:46,206
That is how people naturally act
when they are frightened.

1090
01:00:47,082 --> 01:00:49,125
Even a man can easily become frightened.

1091
01:00:49,709 --> 01:00:51,169
You need not feel sorry.

1092
01:01:01,930 --> 01:01:03,848
No, I'm not sorry at all.

1093
01:01:06,017 --> 01:01:07,143
If I had to go back,

1094
01:01:07,227 --> 01:01:09,771
I would still chase after you
like a madman.

1095
01:01:09,854 --> 01:01:12,607
I'd do something foolish
and blow up at you again.

1096
01:01:13,441 --> 01:01:17,195
Even if you're disappointed in me,
as long as you're okay, I'll be relieved.

1097
01:01:17,862 --> 01:01:19,948
<i>This man is hopeless.</i>

1098
01:01:20,031 --> 01:01:21,908
I'm really sorry for being like this.

1099
01:01:22,492 --> 01:01:25,745
<i>A foolish man</i>
<i>who cannot even apologize properly.</i>

1100
01:01:26,871 --> 01:01:28,999
But I can't help it.
This is how I truly feel.

1101
01:01:29,082 --> 01:01:31,167
<i>A bull-headed lone wolf</i>
<i>who only cares about himself.</i>

1102
01:01:31,251 --> 01:01:32,585
<i>Willful and self-centered.</i>

1103
01:01:33,086 --> 01:01:35,422
<i>Shameless enough to sell</i>
<i>his conscience for money.</i>

1104
01:01:35,505 --> 01:01:36,840
So I'm warning you.

1105
01:01:38,258 --> 01:01:40,385
Listen carefully to what I'm about to say.

1106
01:01:43,513 --> 01:01:45,223
I'm about to do something,

1107
01:01:45,307 --> 01:01:47,392
so if you want to run, now's your chance.

1108
01:01:49,144 --> 01:01:50,562
I'll give you three seconds.

1109
01:01:51,438 --> 01:01:52,647
One.

1110
01:01:53,440 --> 01:01:54,524
Two.

1111
01:01:55,608 --> 01:01:56,735
Three.

1112
01:02:02,949 --> 01:02:05,869
<i>There are countless reasons</i>
<i>I must not fall for this man.</i>

1113
01:02:22,177 --> 01:02:24,220
<i>But there is just one reason</i>

1114
01:02:26,014 --> 01:02:27,265
<i>why I have.</i>

1115
01:02:30,226 --> 01:02:31,895
You grabbed me first.

1116
01:03:26,574 --> 01:03:29,911
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

1117
01:03:30,662 --> 01:03:33,748
"The moon rises, luminous.
The beauty, how lovely."

1118
01:03:33,832 --> 01:03:36,751
"Gracefully entwining, unfolding.
My troubled heart aches."

1119
01:03:41,881 --> 01:03:43,508
"The bright moon rises,

1120
01:03:43,591 --> 01:03:45,343
revealing my beautiful love."

1121
01:03:45,427 --> 01:03:47,512
"It tenderly stirs and blooms."

1122
01:03:50,348 --> 01:03:51,975
"My heart

1123
01:03:52,058 --> 01:03:53,643
aches in longing."

1124
01:03:58,148 --> 01:03:59,190
What?

1125
01:04:05,530 --> 01:04:07,240
-Such irreverence.
-Gosh.

1126
01:04:07,323 --> 01:04:11,077
A junior court lady who has only just had
her initiation is sneaking alcohol?

1127
01:04:11,161 --> 01:04:13,913
Your Highness.
What brings you here this late…

1128
01:04:13,997 --> 01:04:17,083
I came to chase away
the bird chittering through the night.

1129
01:04:17,167 --> 01:04:19,252
And I find a palace attendant who drinks

1130
01:04:19,335 --> 01:04:21,337
inside the palace
in defiance of the liquor ban?

1131
01:04:21,421 --> 01:04:23,381
Do you have a death wish?

1132
01:04:23,465 --> 01:04:25,175
No, it is not that.

1133
01:04:26,050 --> 01:04:27,427
This is…

1134
01:04:27,510 --> 01:04:29,804
This is not alcohol. It is medicine.

1135
01:04:29,888 --> 01:04:32,223
-Medicine?
-Yes, it is medicine.

1136
01:04:32,307 --> 01:04:35,685
I picked the ingredients myself
in the scorching summer heat to brew

1137
01:04:36,478 --> 01:04:37,479
this fine medicine.

1138
01:04:37,562 --> 01:04:41,357
Medicinal liquor for the ailing
is exempt from the ban.

1139
01:04:41,441 --> 01:04:42,859
Is that what you mean?

1140
01:04:42,942 --> 01:04:45,028
Then tell me, my companion.

1141
01:04:45,778 --> 01:04:47,989
What ails you to drink
this medicinal liquor?

1142
01:04:48,740 --> 01:04:50,074
Well,

1143
01:04:50,158 --> 01:04:51,326
you see…

1144
01:04:53,119 --> 01:04:55,079
I suffer greatly from suppressed anger,

1145
01:04:55,747 --> 01:04:57,582
so I use alcohol as medicine.

1146
01:04:58,374 --> 01:05:00,793
Rather than being consumed
by this rage within,

1147
01:05:00,877 --> 01:05:02,420
is it not better to drink

1148
01:05:03,254 --> 01:05:04,839
and stay alive?

1149
01:05:06,257 --> 01:05:07,592
That mouth of yours

1150
01:05:08,259 --> 01:05:10,345
is just too smart for its own good.

1151
01:05:11,304 --> 01:05:14,140
-Stop smiling.
-You complained when I looked too grim.

1152
01:05:15,016 --> 01:05:16,684
Now you scold me for smiling?

1153
01:05:16,768 --> 01:05:18,520
Yes, stop smiling.

1154
01:05:19,938 --> 01:05:21,147
You look ugly.

1155
01:06:12,949 --> 01:06:14,075
<i>A deserted island?</i>

1156
01:06:14,158 --> 01:06:16,786
<i>I have not committed any sins.</i>
<i>Why have I been exiled here?</i>

1157
01:06:16,869 --> 01:06:17,912
<i>There's nothing we can do.</i>

1158
01:06:17,996 --> 01:06:19,581
<i>We'll just have to make</i>
<i>a cozy little life together.</i>

1159
01:06:19,664 --> 01:06:20,546
I have no memory of that.

1160
01:06:20,616 --> 01:06:22,458
You will never be able
to take back what happened yesterday.

1161
01:06:22,542 --> 01:06:24,115
I really need to quit drinking.

1162
01:06:24,190 --> 01:06:27,338
<i>Let's shoot him down</i>
<i>when he reaches the apex.</i>

1163
01:06:27,422 --> 01:06:28,339
<i>D-Day should be…</i>

1164
01:06:28,423 --> 01:06:29,924
What's your relationship with Se-gye?

1165
01:06:30,008 --> 01:06:32,010
Se-gye and I are going to be married.

1166
01:06:32,093 --> 01:06:33,928
Goodness! Ma'am!

1167
01:06:34,012 --> 01:06:36,556
Mr. Cha, did you drive
under the influence?

1168
01:06:36,639 --> 01:06:38,600
Do what you must to keep her
out of the press.

1169
01:06:38,683 --> 01:06:40,476
Just stop doing anything for me.

1170
01:06:40,560 --> 01:06:41,936
<i>If you keep making me waver,</i>

1171
01:06:42,020 --> 01:06:44,606
I will shamelessly start hoping for more.

1172
01:06:47,025 --> 01:06:49,027
Subtitle translation by Justin S. Kim

